111.6	Hiroshima	Hiroshima	Hiroshima Hiroshima-shi) ) is the capital of Hiroshima Prefecture, and the largest city in the Chūgoku region of western Honshu, the largest island of Japan. It is best known as the first city in history to be destroyed by a nuclear weapon when the United States Army Air Forces (USAAF) dropped an atomic bomb on it at 8:15 A.M. on August 6, 1945, near the end of World War II. Its name 広島 means "Wide Island".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Hiroshima_montage.jpg/250px-Hiroshima_montage.jpg
